<p>President Trump will host Syrian President Ahmed al-Sharaa at the White House on November 10, a visit described by officials as the first-ever by a Syrian head of state to the U.S. presidential residence . U.S. and Syrian officials say the meeting is intended as a diplomatic opening to discuss Syria’s reconstruction and broader regional security, reflecting a step toward formal engagement after earlier contacts this year . The date and visit were confirmed publicly by U.S. envoy Tom Barrack, who has been leading U.S. engagement with Damascus .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/5ruPOCK992C6o6k9kV-NXvwkBInHgHV9Gg7Ln-KU6pLKGRa8Q3Mx65i5zbkjqONLLqhc20x_to2YhvfcsDdqwh8C78G-C3Fi5icPNsCV95gwN6aLoTxBYL67D9F2P0U_Jp5_oOuzB6-M7TzXGHGw_q1IfGgaM97USQLJLg' alt='Syrian President Ahmed al-Sharaa (file photo).' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Security push: U.S. officials are reported to be pushing for a Syria–Israel security agreement to be reached by the time of the visit .</li><li>Counter‑ISIS tie: Syrian leadership is expected to sign an agreement to join a U.S.-led coalition against ISIS during visits or talks tied to the new engagement .</li><li>Envoy confirmation: Tom Barrack, serving as the U.S. special envoy to Syria (and U.S. ambassador to Turkey), publicly confirmed al-Sharaa’s Washington trip and helped arrange talks .</li><li>Earlier contact: President Trump and Ahmed al-Sharaa met in Saudi Arabia in May, a prior encounter that set the stage for continued diplomatic engagement .</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>U.S. special envoy (Tom Barrack): Barrack confirmed the November 10 visit and has served as the U.S. point person arranging engagement with Syria, framing the trip as part of diplomatic outreach . (<a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/syria-president-ahmed-al-sharaa-washington-visit-november/'>CBS News</a>)</li><li>Syrian foreign ministry (Asad al-Shaibani): Syrian officials say al-Sharaa will raise reconstruction on the agenda during his Washington trip, signaling Damascus’ priority for rebuilding talks . (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/syrian-president-will-visit-white-house-in-early-november-foreign-minister-says'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>Syrian source cited by Israeli press: A Syrian source told reporters the U.S. is pressing for a security agreement between Syria and Israel to be in place by the visit, tying the trip to broader regional arrangements . (<a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/trump-to-host-sharaa-in-1st-ever-visit-by-a-syrian-president-to-white-house-officials/'>Times of Israel</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/2/trump-to-host-syrias-al-sharaa-for-talks-at-white-house-envoy-says'>Trump to host Syria’s al-Sharaa for talks at White House, envoy says</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/trump-to-host-sharaa-in-1st-ever-visit-by-a-syrian-president-to-white-house-officials/'>Trump to host Sharaa in 1st-ever visit by a Syrian president to White House — officials</a> - timesofisrael.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/syria-president-ahmed-al-sharaa-washington-visit-november/'>Syrian leader to meet Trump at White House this month, U.S. envoy says</a> - cbsnews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/trump-to-host-al-sharaa-making-him-first-syrian-president-invited-to-oval-office-says-envoy-13947154.html'>Trump to host al-Sharaa, making him first Syrian president invited to Oval Office, says envoy</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/trump-to-host-syrias-ahmed-sharaa-in-1st-ever-visit-by-syrian-leader-to-us-9558369#publisher=newsstand'>Trump To Host Syria&#x27;s Ahmed Sharaa In 1st-Ever Visit By Syrian Leader To US</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/syrian-president-will-visit-white-house-in-early-november-foreign-minister-says'>Syrian president will visit White House in early Nove